A vintage 1970s technical illustration style image depicting a massive filing cabinet server tower stretching impossibly tall, with countless drawers partially open and overflowing with colorful paper documents, manila folders, and sealed envelopes cascading down like a waterfall. The cabinet sits in a retro computer room with orange shag carpet and wood-paneled walls. Tiny workers in bell-bottom pants climb ladders along the cabinet, desperately trying to catch the falling papers. A large analog gauge on the side of the cabinet shows a needle in the red zone. Warm amber lighting casts long shadows, with dust particles visible in the air. The scene conveys overwhelming digital storage burden through a nostalgic physical metaphor.
